  <span id="freeText1815082642714163872" style="display:none">Most of the books I have been rereading I read in high school and have been giving very different ratings (lower stars now that I’m older and have better perspective then I did back then). However, this book I have rated 5 stars again. While reading it, I was able to feel the spirit multiple times because I already know that Joseph Smith was a prophet of God and that He really did see God and Jesus Christ. My heart felt sad for the characters in the book that struggled with Joseph and the ability to let loved ones follow their beliefs. I am so grateful for religious freedom and the ability that I have to worship as I please.<br />I am excited to read the next book as I have not read the rest of them before! :) </span>
